(11,2,'1. Structural Integrity','<li><strong>Description:</strong> The project must ensure that all structures, including buildings, roads, bridges, and other infrastructures, meet the highest standards of stability and strength. This is essential for the safety of the public and the longevity of the structures.</li><li><strong>Requirement:</strong> Compliance with national building codes and international structural standards to prevent any future collapse or degradation.</li>','admin','2025-01-31 15:41:43',NULL,NULL,1,2,NULL,1),
(12,2,'2. Safety Standards','<li><strong>Description:</strong> The project must be designed and constructed in a way that prioritizes the safety of workers, residents, and future users. This includes proper signage, safety barriers, and emergency access routes.</li><li><strong>Requirement:</strong> All safety regulations and protocols must be adhered to during both construction and post-construction phases.</li>','admin','2025-01-31 15:42:09',NULL,NULL,1,2,NULL,2),
(13,2,'3. Sustainability','<li><strong>Description:</strong> The project should incorporate sustainable design practices, such as energy-efficient systems, eco-friendly materials, and green building technologies, to reduce the environmental impact.</li><li><strong>Requirement:</strong> Use of renewable resources, waste reduction techniques, and adherence to sustainable urban planning principles.</li>','admin','2025-01-31 15:42:28',NULL,NULL,1,2,NULL,3),
(14,2,'4. Accessibility','<li><strong>Description:</strong> Ensuring the urban space is easily accessible to people with all abilities, including those with physical disabilities, is a critical requirement.</li><li><strong>Requirement:</strong> Designs must include ramps, elevators, wide doorways, and pathways that adhere to accessibility guidelines like the ADA (Americans with Disabilities Act).</li>','admin','2025-01-31 15:42:48',NULL,NULL,1,2,NULL,4),
(15,2,'5. Water Management','<li><strong>Description:</strong> The project must effectively manage water resources to prevent flooding, ensure proper drainage, and promote water conservation practices.</li><li><strong>Requirement:</strong> Installation of drainage systems, stormwater management, and rainwater harvesting technologies to control water flow and minimize waste.</li>','admin','2025-01-31 15:43:09',NULL,NULL,1,2,NULL,5),
(16,2,'6. Quality of Materials','<li><strong>Description:</strong> The materials used must be durable, high-quality, and suited for the local climate and conditions. This will ensure that the infrastructure lasts longer and requires fewer repairs.</li><li><strong>Requirement:</strong> Materials must be sourced from certified suppliers and meet international quality standards to ensure they withstand wear and tear.</li>','admin','2025-01-31 15:43:32',NULL,NULL,1,2,NULL,6),
(17,2,'7. Environmental Impact Assessment','<li><strong>Description:</strong> A comprehensive evaluation of the projects impact on the surrounding environment should be conducted. This includes assessing air quality, noise pollution, biodiversity, and ecosystem disruption.</li><li><strong>Requirement:</strong> A formal Environmental Impact Assessment (EIA) should be conducted and any negative impacts mitigated to meet environmental standards.</li>','admin','2025-01-31 15:44:08',NULL,NULL,1,2,NULL,7),
(18,2,'8. Traffic and Transportation Planning','<li><strong>Description:</strong> The project must address traffic flow, pedestrian movement, and public transportation to ensure the area is well-connected and not congested.</li><li><strong>Requirement:</strong> Proper design of roads, sidewalks, bus stops, and parking spaces to avoid bottlenecks and facilitate smooth transportation.</li>','admin','2025-01-31 15:44:31',NULL,NULL,1,2,NULL,8),
(19,2,'9. Community Engagement','<li><strong>Description:</strong> The project should involve the local community in the planning and decision-making process, ensuring that it meets the needs of those who will live and work in the area.</li><li><strong>Requirement:</strong> Regular public consultations, surveys, and feedback mechanisms to engage community members throughout the planning and construction phases.</li>','admin','2025-01-31 15:44:53',NULL,NULL,1,2,NULL,9),
(20,2,'10. Risk Management','<li><strong>Description:</strong> Potential risks (such as natural disasters, fire, structural failure, etc.) must be identified and mitigated throughout the design and construction process.</li><li><strong>Requirement:</strong> Implementation of risk assessment strategies, including seismic analysis, fire safety systems, and flood protection measures.</li>','admin','2025-01-31 15:45:13',NULL,NULL,1,2,NULL,10),
(21,2,'11. Utility Infrastructure',NULL,'admin','2025-01-31 15:45:35',NULL,NULL,1,2,NULL,11),
(22,2,'12. Aesthetic Appeal and Urban Design','<li><strong>Description:</strong> A visually pleasing and well-planned urban environment can enhance the quality of life and promote a sense of community. Aesthetic elements, such as landscaping, building designs, and public spaces, should be carefully considered.</li><li><strong>Requirement:</strong> Thoughtful urban design that complements the surrounding environment, incorporates green spaces, and meets the aesthetic preferences of the community.</li>','admin','2025-01-31 15:45:59',NULL,NULL,1,2,NULL,12);

